Secretary to Parliament Gengezi Mgidlana told journalists that the traditional after-Sona dinner would not take place due to budgetary constraints. CAPE TOWN - It s up to National Assembly Speaker Baleka Mbete to spell out who is footing the bill for the Speaker s Ball she s hosting after President Jacob Zuma s State of the Nation Address (Sona).Deputy Speaker Lechesa Tsenoli says he ll put the request to Mbete.Invitations bearing Mbete s picture for cocktails and dinner at a plush Camps Bay hotel have sparked controversy.Last week, secretary to Parliament Gengezi Mgidlana told journalists that the traditional after-Sona dinner would not take place due to budgetary constraints.Tsenoli has confirmed he ll be attending the Speaker s Ball after President Zuma s Sona address.But he could not answer the question about who was paying for it. I don t know who funds the Speaker s Ball, I ll be attending for the first time this year. I have no clue who funds it. We ll ask that question, we ll ask the Speaker when she has an opportunity to interact with you. In future we ll ask her to do that. Yes, tomorrow she will be able to give you that information. Both the African National Congress and Parliament have said they have nothing to do with the event.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)